    oneLineHook: "A country doctor who named giant reptiles while the establishment dismissed his claims.",
    knownFor: "Identified and named Iguanodon in 1825 - only the second dinosaur formally described, and the first large herbivorous one - then spent a career identifying Sussex's Cretaceous fauna against sustained institutional resistance.",
