    oneLineHook: "He named dinosaurs, built the cathedral that houses them, and was regarded with suspicion by almost everyone who worked with him.",
    knownFor: "Coined the term 'Dinosauria' in 1842, grouping previously isolated fossil reptiles into a recognised taxonomic class - and founded what became the Natural History Museum in London.",
