    id: "jose-bonaparte",
    name: "José Bonaparte",
    dates: "1928–2020",
    role: "Vertebrate palaeontologist",
    oneLineHook: "He remade the map of dinosaur evolution by showing that South America was a world apart.",
    knownFor: "Named Carnotaurus, Abelisaurus, Amargasaurus, Mussaurus, and dozens of other South American dinosaurs - demonstrating that Gondwanan continents harboured entirely separate evolutionary lineages from the Northern Hemisphere genera that dominated museum collections.",
    eraCategory: "Southern continents & global palaeontology",
